starts off slow and sort of rips off that “Knocking
on Heaven’s.Door” chord change. It mixes that
with a cliched soul segue into a chorus that gives
this writer some hope: “Life is sweet  If you let
me, I could help you see.” Its almost pointless to
discuss the rest of the songs, but one does stand
out. “You Hurt Me” is the cheesiest song on the
